        "timestamp": "2018-04-25 19:37:07.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nWhen I changed these classes I was worried that it wasn't thread safe. The old class was pretty much a static class but the new library insists on an instance existing because it's implemented by specializing an abstract class.\n\nThe current implementation is a singleton but I'm not sure that the singleton doesn't get overwritten on new connections. If it does, we'd get all sorts of interesting side effects. I don't really understand how the class is being called in the engine.\n\nIf its OK with you I'd like to have a look at it in a little more detail later tonight/in the morning.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "e445b3ff601c0aad14fd462bc82ad11601d8391d",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 2757,
